Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Gender Inequality in China; Smokestack Nostalgia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b044h9pv
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 2 Jun 2014
Chinese women & the resurgence of gender inequality. Laurie Taylor talks to Leta Hong Fincher, about 'Leftover Women', her study of the pressures facing Modern Chinese women who are often locked out of social equality, property rights, and legal protection from domestic abuse. Also, 'smokestack nostalgia' - the meaning of post-industrial imagery. Tim Stangleman, Professor of Sociology at the University of Kent, questions the continuing desire to reflect back and find value in our industrial past. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less